-- China stocks end up more than 2 pct on late rally
-- By the Shanghai Newsroom
-- Wed Dec 31, 2014 02:29AM EST
-- None



SHANGHAI, Dec 31 (Reuters) - China stocks closed up more than 2 percent on Wednesday, boosted by a late afternoon rally which helped the stock market become the best performer among major global bourses this year.

The CSI300 index <.CSI300> of the largest listed companies in Shanghai and Shenzhen rose 2.2 percent, to 3,533.71 to end up 51.7 percent for the year.